1 cost to the employee. The training may be offered through any method of training identified in subsection (4).
2 (4) The legislature recommends that employees Employees under subsection (3) shall take at
3 least 2 hours of youth suicide awareness and prevention training every 5 years. Appropriate methods for
4 delivery of the training include:
5 (a) in-person attendance at a live training;
6 (b) videoconference;
7 (c) an individual program of study of designated materials;
8 (d) self-review modules available online; and
9 (e) any other method chosen by the local school board that is consistent with professional
10 development standards.
11 (5) The trustees of a school district shall establish policies, procedures, or plans related to suicide
12 prevention and response. The policies, procedures, or plans must include a description of the youth suicide
13 awareness and prevention training requirements for school district employees pursuant to subsections (3) and
14 (4).
15 (6) No cause of action may be brought for any loss or damage caused by any act or omission
16 resulting from the implementation of the provisions of this section or resulting from any training or lack of
17 training related to this section. Nothing in this section may be construed to impose a specific duty of care."
18
19 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
